     7	/// @title BitmaskVerifier
     8	/// @notice Verifier contract implementing selective calldata hashing using bitmasking rules.
     9	/// @dev Enables flexible permissioning by allowing dynamic verification of transaction intent through partial data matching.
    10	contract BitmaskVerifier is ICustomVerifier {
    11	    /// @notice Computes a hash of a call using selective masking over its fields.
    12	    /// @dev The hash is computed in the following sequence:
    13	    /// 1. Hashing `who` using `bitmask[0:32]`
    14	    /// 2. Hashing `where` using `bitmask[32:64]`
    15	    /// 3. Hashing `value` using `bitmask[64:96]`
    16	    /// 4. Iteratively hashing each byte of `data` masked with `bitmask[i + 96]`
    17	    ///
    18	    /// This allows whitelisting specific parts of calldata or sender/target/value.
    19	    ///
    20	    /// @param bitmask A byte array encoding which bytes should be included in the hash.
